data.title: Charlie Villanueva, Basketball Player
data.meta_description: Charlie Villanueva stats and bio. Stats averages season by season. Quick access to game by game stats.
data.text:
Charlie Villanueva - Points

Charlie Villanueva scores a career high 48 points (2006)

On March 26, 2006, Charlie Villanueva set his career high in points in a NBA game. That day he scored 48 points in Toronto's road loss against Milwaukee, 125-116. He also had 9 rebounds, 3 assists, 1 steal. He shot 14/21 from two, 6/11 from three, shooting at 62.5% from the field. He also shot 2/3 from the free-throw line.

Charlie Villanueva - Rebounds

Charlie Villanueva grabs a career high 18 rebounds (2006)

On April 02, 2006, Charlie Villanueva set his career high in rebounds in a NBA game. That day he grabbed 18 rebounds in Toronto's home loss against New Orleans, 113-120. He also had 25 points, 2 assists and 1 block.

Charlie Villanueva - Assists

Charlie Villanueva gives a career high 6 assists (2009)

On January 31, 2009, Charlie Villanueva tied his career high in assists in a NBA game. That day he dished 6 assists in Milwaukee's home win against Atlanta, 110-107. He also had 27 points, 7 rebounds.

Charlie Villanueva - Steals

Charlie Villanueva has a career high 4 steals (2005)

On November 18, 2005, Charlie Villanueva tied his career high in steals in a NBA game. That day he reached 4 steals in Toronto's road loss against Boston, 100-93. He also had 18 points, 6 rebounds.

Charlie Villanueva - Blocks

Charlie Villanueva blocks a career high 6 shots (2005)

On January 15, 2005, Charlie Villanueva set his career high in blocks in a NCAA game. That day he went for 6 blocks in Connecticut Huskies's home win against Rutgers Scarlet Knights, 78-64. He also had 14 points, 14 rebounds and 4 assists.

Charlie Villanueva - Efficiency

Charlie Villanueva records a career high 45 efficiency rating (2006)

On March 26, 2006, Charlie Villanueva set his career high in efficiency in a NBA game. That day he accomplished 45 efficiency in Toronto's road loss against Milwaukee, 125-116. He also had 48 points, 9 rebounds and 3 assists.
